### üéØ My assessment: Is this a ‚Äútop-level‚Äù IEEE conference?

Here‚Äôs a breakdown of what to look at and how this one stacks up:

**What supports credibility:**

* It is technically *co-sponsored* by a local IEEE Section: IEEE Madhya Pradesh Section. ([oriental.ac.in][1])
* It has a posted IEEE Record Number (#67170), which means it is listed as a conference in the IEEE database. ([oriental.ac.in][1])
* The website states that accepted & presented papers will be submitted for inclusion in IEEE Xplore, which is a positive sign. ([oriental.ac.in][2])
* Very broad track coverage ‚Äî good if your paper falls into one of their listed areas.

**What raises caution / things to check:**

* Even though they say ‚Äúwill only be submitted to IEEE Xplore‚Äù, note the phrase *‚Äúsubject to meeting IEEE Xplore's scope and quality requirements‚Äù*. That means submission ‚â† guaranteed inclusion.
* Because it is a **first edition** (‚Äú1st International Conference on ‚Ä¶‚Äù) according to their page. ([oriental.ac.in][1]) First-time conferences can vary widely in reputation, review rigour, and visibility.
* Being regionally organised (in Bhopal) and by an institute rather than a long-standing flagship IEEE conference means the ‚Äúprestige‚Äù may not be comparable to major long-running IEEE flagship conferences (e.g., those invited by large IEEE societies).
* For ‚Äútop-level‚Äù in academia you often check factors like: long history, high impact, rigorous acceptance rate, strong global programme committee, whether proceedings have been reliably indexed in IEEE Xplore for past years, whether the conference is listed in major rankings (e.g., CORE, Scopus, etc). I did *not* find independent evidence of past editions with large citations or verifying indexing reliably yet.

**My conclusion:**
Yes, it *is* a legitimate IEEE-recorded conference with IEEE co-sponsorship and the mechanism for publication in IEEE Xplore. That means it is **reasonably credible**, especially if you are a student or researcher wanting a peer-reviewed venue.
However ‚Äî if by ‚Äútop-level‚Äù you mean the most selective, highly-cited flagship conferences in your field (with brand-name recognition, very low acceptance rates, perhaps invited keynotes, etc) ‚Äî then this one might **not** yet rank at that top tier. It‚Äôs more of a good regional/international conference rather than a global ‚Äútop 10 in the world‚Äù venue.

